Van Rompuy Asked Berlusconi for Reassurances on Italy Measures

-- B y   P a t r i c k   H e n r y
-- 
2011-10-23T15:06:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-23/van-rompuy-asked-berlusconi-for-reassurances-on-italy-measures.html
European Union President  Herman Van
Rompuy  said he asked Italian Prime Minister  Silvio Berlusconi 
for assurances on the Italian government’s austerity measures in
a Brussels meeting today.  Van Rompuy  said it’s important that investors are reassured
on  Italy , he told reporters after an EU summit in Brussels
today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
